/*
 * @topic : What is Protractor?
 * @definition : Protractor is an end-to-end test framework for Angular and AngularJS
 *             application. generally, (WebDriver + Angular Support = Protractor.)
 * @tags :  <theory> <practice>
 *
 * @note:  Disclaimer: but Protractor makes your life easy. 
 * 			If something changes in the future you should be ready. So, make a habit of reading the 
 * 			official websites.
 * 			To know the version of node-module type : "node-module --version"
 * 			If you see tests are failing in protractor is failing after latest release 
 * 			then you should updata the webdriver-manager by typing: "webdriver-manager update"
 */
 
 VVVVVVVVVVVVVVVVVVVV starts here VVVVVVVVVVVVVVVVVV

  POINTS TO NOTE: 

	1. Selenium WebDriver can be used to automate Angualar Apps but there are some Angualar features
		Which may or may not be handled by WebDriver. Or WebDriver is little inconsistent with little core
		features of Angular Application. 
		Also, somehow to make those features work you need to do alot of coding using selenium WebDriver.

	2. WHAT IS JASMINE?
		Jasmine is unit testing framework for e.g. In Selenium you might have come accross the unit testing 
		Frameworks like TestNG. Junit. Its same but for JavaScript/Protractor.
		Jasmine is an open-source testing framework for JavaScript. It aims to run on any JavaScript-enabled 
		platform, to not intrude on the application nor the IDE, and to have easy-to-read syntax.

	3. ### NOTES ON NODE.JS ###
 
		Q. What Node.js? 
		A. chorme v8 js engine topped with c++.

		Q. What is npm?
		A. npm stands for node package manager. It is used to install software which are
			available in node repository. Protractor is hosted in node repository.

	4. 	Points: you will need Selenium-server to connect your protractor test cases to your 
		actual browser. Its basically like selenuim Grid or appium. 

	5. 	The server needs to be started in order to start any testing with protractor. Your protractor
		code will send a request to the server which control your local browser accordingly. 
 
