		### DIFFERENCE BETWEEN TYPESCRIPT AND JAVASCRIPT ###
		1. TypeScript is not a new language.
		2. it is superset of JavaScript.
		3. JavaScript + Few Additional features (OOPS)	= TypeScript.
		4. No matter you use JS or TS, Protractor API Remains same in syntaxes and is originally 
			built in JS. Differences arises in syntaxs when building the Test framework for Protractor.
		5. 2 different Framework Jasmine(JavaScript) and Cuccumber(TypeScript).
		
		NOTES on The Differences:
		> 	oops concept in JS is fairly new and brought in during ES5 release.]
		>	But the concept of oops are still lacking in JS which are more visible in TypeScript.
		> 	The Protractor API syntax is same for TS and JS. For e.g. clicking a button or sending 
			the keys all are same for TS and JS.
		>	When you start building a framework then you are going to see alot of changes in TS and JS.
			for e.g. when you use PO pattern to drive data from one page to another page.

