 closure:
	At the end we finally found answers for the questions like.
	Q.	Why Protractor? 
		-The only stable framework to Automate Angular Apps. It is developed and maintained by Angular Team.
		***Selenium*** is still king but for Angular Apps Protractor takes the edge. For all the cutting edge 
		Technologies like React.js, Angular.js and Vue.js for all of this ***Protractor*** is very stable.
		and is by default supports all the angular apps as developed by the same devs.

	Q. What language does Protractor Support?
		-Protractor is a Node.js program built on top of WebDriverJS. So it uses JavaScript as core language 
		to develop tests. So, core Protractor is Selenium WebDriver for JS and top of it they used some wrapper 
		classes to support angular apps. And as with selenium those wrapper classes are not compulsory but then it
		would take alot of years to get through simple things which could be done in minutes. That's why you use 
		JavaScript(TypeScript is optional) as the core language to make Protractor applications.

	Q. Why Protractor have huge demand in the market?
		-I do not have JavaScript knowledege. Can I follow this Tutorial? Absolutely. Everthing from Scratch.

	Q. Even if your Application becomes non Angular somehow even then Protractor supports non-angular Apps
		As well. 

	Q. What are the tools/languages are used to automate angualar Apps?
		-Node.js, Jasmine, JavaScript and Protractor API.

